.TH "WEBTRANSPORT.GETSTATS" "3JS" "February 24, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
WebTransport.getStats \- WebTransport: getStats() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Secure context:\f[R] This feature is available only in secure
contexts (HTTPS).
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]getStats()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]WebTransport\f[R] interface asynchronously returns an object
containing HTTP/3 connection statistics.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
getStats()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
A \f[CR]Promise\f[R] that resolves to an object containing HTTP/3
connection statistics.
The returned object may have the following properties/statistics:
.TP
\f[B]timestamp\f[R]
A \f[CR]DOMHighResTimeStamp\f[R] indicating the timestamp at which the
statistics were gathered, relative to Jan 1, 1970, UTC.
.TP
\f[B]bytesSent\f[R]
A positive integer indicating the number of bytes sent on the QUIC
connection, including retransmissions.
Note that this count does not include additional data from protocols
used by QUIC, such as UDP, or any other outer framing.
.TP
\f[B]packetsSent\f[R]
A positive integer indicating the number of packets sent on the QUIC
connection, including those that are known to have been lost.
.TP
\f[B]packetsLost\f[R]
A positive integer indicating the number of packets lost on the QUIC
connection.
This value will increase as packets are declared lost, and decrease if
they are subsequently received.
.TP
\f[B]numOutgoingStreamsCreated\f[R]
A positive integer indicating the number of outgoing QUIC streams
created on the QUIC connection.
.TP
\f[B]numIncomingStreamsCreated\f[R]
A positive integer indicating the number of incoming QUIC streams
created on the QUIC connection.
.TP
\f[B]bytesReceived\f[R]
A positive integer indicating the total number of bytes received on the
QUIC connection.
This count includes duplicate data from streams, but does not include
additional data for protocols used by QUIC, such as UDP, or any other
outer framing.
.TP
\f[B]packetsReceived\f[R]
A positive integer indicating the total number of packets received on
the QUIC connection, including packets that were not processable.
.TP
\f[B]smoothedRtt\f[R]
A \f[CR]DOMHighResTimeStamp\f[R] containing the smoothed round\-trip
time (RTT) currently observed on the connection, calculated as an
exponentially weighted moving average of an endpoint\(cqs RTT samples
after taking account of acknowledgement delays.
.TP
\f[B]rttVariation\f[R]
A \f[CR]DOMHighResTimeStamp\f[R] containing the mean variation in
round\-trip time samples currently observed on the connection.
.TP
\f[B]minRtt\f[R]
A \f[CR]DOMHighResTimeStamp\f[R] containing the minimum round\-trip time
observed on the entire connection.
.TP
\f[B]datagrams\f[R]
An object containing statistics for datagram transmission over the
connection.
The object has the following properties:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]timestamp\f[R]
A \f[CR]DOMHighResTimeStamp\f[R] indicating the timestamp at which the
statistics were gathered, relative to Jan 1, 1970, UTC.
.TP
\f[B]expiredOutgoing\f[R]
A positive integer indicating the number of datagrams that were dropped
from the queue for sending because they expired.
Note that the maximum age before a datagram in the send\-queue expires
can be found in \f[CR]outgoingMaxAge\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]droppedIncoming\f[R]
A positive integer indicating the number incoming datagrams that were
dropped.
Incoming datagrams are dropped if the application does not read them
before new datagrams overflow the \f[CR]readable\f[R] stream receive
queue.
.TP
\f[B]lostOutgoing\f[R]
A positive integer indicating the number of sent datagrams that were
declared lost.
Note that a datagram may be declared lost if, for example, no
acknowledgement arrived within a timeout, or an acknowledgement for a
later datagram was received first.
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
The example below uses \f[CR]await\f[R] to wait on the
\f[CR]Promise\f[R] returned by \f[CR]getStats()\f[R].
When the promise fulfills, the result for the \f[CR]bytesSent\f[R]
property in the stats object is logged to the console.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] stats = \f[B]await\f[R] transport.getStats();
console.log(\(gaBytes send: ${stats.bytesSent}\(ga);
.EE
